column5: figured i would share a vid from a couple of seasons ago. 39" 17lb burbot my brother caught! i believe if you look it up its the unofficial Ontario record, but why kill it for course fish "fame"!  its cheeks touched each side of an 8" hole!        http://s156.beta.photobucket.com/user/jfps6/media/MVI_0795.mp4.html  http://s156.beta.photobucket.com/user/jfps6/media/MVI_0796.mp4.html
Amazing fish.  Fantastic eating as well.
Awesome! Was that from simcoe? We get some massive specimens from nip each year too.  I know Joey says fantstic eating, but I'd consider it closer to "decent". Haha sorry Joey
oh yeah thats simcoe alright!  love the xterra pic, man i miss that beast!
